Title : Template:Luke-Riders/doc
Text : {{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Categories go at the bottom of this page and interwikis go in Wikidata. -->
This template generates a book citation as above, using the {{tlx|cite book}} template.

=== Usage ===
 <nowiki>{{Luke-Riders | page=xx}}</nowiki>
 <nowiki>{{Luke-Riders | pages=xx–yy}}</nowiki>
 <nowiki>{{Luke-Riders | ref=ID}}</nowiki>

;Optional parameters:
* '''page''' – The relevant page number for a specific citation – the "p." prefix is automatically added
* '''pages''' – The relevant page numbers for a specific citation – the "pp." prefix is automatically added
If both {{para|page}} and {{para|pages}} are specified, {{para|page}} is ignored.
* '''ref''' – ID for anchor; if omitted, the special value {{para|ref|harv}} is used, so that {{tlx|harvnb|Luke|1997|7=p=FOO}} etc. will link.
Apart from the default value {{para|ref|harv}}, the three parameters are passed unchanged to {{tlx|cite book}} - see [[Template:Cite book/doc|that template's documentation]] for further information.

